\frac{1}{2\pi i} \int_C \left( \frac{x}{n} \right)^s \frac{ds}{s} = \theta(x-n).
x\in \mathbb{R}, x\geq 0
C = \{s:\operatorname{Re}(s) = \sigma\}
\sigma > 0
t = \operatorname{Im}(s)
x/n\gt0
