 \int_Cx^{\large s}\frac{\mathrm{d}s}{s} =\int_Ce^{\large s\log(x)}\frac{\mathrm{d}s}{s} 
 \frac1{2\pi i}\int_Cx^{\large s}\frac{\mathrm{d}s}{s}=1 
 \frac1{2\pi i}\int_Cx^{\large s}\frac{\mathrm{d}s}{s}=0 
 \begin{align} \frac1{2\pi i}\int_Cx^{\large s}\frac{\mathrm{d}s}{s} &=\frac1{2\pi i}\lim_{t\to\infty}\log\left(\frac{\sigma+it}{\sigma-it}\right)\\ &=\frac1{2\pi i}\pi i\\ &=\frac12 \end{align} 
 \theta(x)=\left\{\begin{array}{} 1&\text{if }x\gt0\\ \tfrac12&\text{if }x=0\\ 0&\text{if }x\lt0 \end{array}\right. 
